column1: great gaming motherboard the installation was very easy thanks to the instructions and the design is very clean i highly recommend this board
i9 12900k 3080ti msi mag z690 build and it perfectly fits what i was expecting looks amazing too really high quality
really great price and the motherboard is solid i have always had good experiences with the msi brand

excellent motherboard this is my second from msi the first being the z390 tomahawk that i loved i decided to continue my adventure with msi

extremely easy to set up the bios is easy to understand even for beginners

several possibilities of expansion on the memory and m2 side i already love it
great mobo great price heart of my new build with a 12600k easy to install and get going 0 issues so far

i got this motherboard a few weeks ago and its been working like a dream it was really easy to install and overall i had no problem with it interacting with any parts for the rest of my computer for the price this board is honestly incredible and i fully recommend it to anyone whos in need of a great motherboard

grabbed this on sale during prime day awesome motherboard that was super easy to build with was able to update the bios using the bios flashback button to use my 13th gen intel cpu overall would recommend this motherboard on sale

upgrading to this motherboard was one of the best and easiest decisions compatible with windows 11 as well i really appreciate the added heat sync for the memory cards i just wish there was a temp gauge to show the cpu temp like some of the other msi boards have

got a great deal on this motherboard at 21500 cad and it has proved to be best in its class so far pairing with the intel 12700k this motherboard has been very easy to work with the design is well thought out and there are great guides out there for setting this up would recommend for those looking at starting a higher end build

i used this for my first ever build it was very easy to work with and the instructions and diagrams in the manual made it a breeze the bios is very user friendly and i was able to get all the settings i wanted so far it has performed phenomenally i highly recommend this motherboard

bought this motherboard for my first pc build and it was very easy to install and seems wellmade and durable i chose this model since i need a mobo with builtin wifi and this fulfills my expectations entirely 1010
i love this mother board best one i had in year got bluetooth 25g lan lots of storage great for all my harddrives and you can use all the ports with out it disabling any of them
very good motherboard for the price little bit rgb would be great

easy to assemble and configure it offers abundant resources and is very stable so far
it looks very good and finishes as well
this was my first time building a pc and this mobo made it easy it feels like quality material and has more to offer than i need overall great product and would buy again
nice mobo the 4 m2 slots is nice

very sturdy motherboard bios was very easy to navigate through
looks good in my case lots of fan headers and the coolers built in for the m2 keep the ssds very cool
i would buy this again if i built another pc

received this motherboard recently installed into a system with i7 12700k and rtx 3090ti very high quality construction had no issues installing and the manual included contains all the info needed to do so properly very happy with this motherboard so far will update if there are any issues
good motherboard msi is reliable i got it for the wifi and the wifi is good plenty of storage with the 4 m2 slots and easy to build with
very well built i chose this over the mag and mpg because of the simplistic design it works perfectly for my build with no rgbs

easy to install
like it a lot so far
it came well packaged easy to install and has a nice bios page easy m2 slot no fuss with the io shield had all the ports i needed
bought this for a pc with 3070 and i7 12700k works and look great
very high quality product great price works perfect our of the box with no issues

came from another msi board z690 a pro integrated io shield is very nice connected both nvme drive with no issue and this board had wifi which helped when i reinstalled windows 11

an added bonus for this board being stealth black it looks nice in my corsair 4000d airflow with minimal rgb

not really a rgb fan so this straight blacked out style gives my pc the look perfect for me probably one of the best ddr4 z690 motherboards this offers a great number of io and fits perfectly in my fractal c as a first time builder it was easy to install and offers 4 nvme ssd slots for future proofing and tons of heatsinks
works right out of the box post with no issues very strong feature set on this board for the price

i bought this motherboard becuase it was rated as an a tier motherboard in the motherboard tier list and is the best midrange z690 board im not going to build my pc until intel 13th gen comes out but bought this motherboard now as it was on sale for prime day
install was straightforward with solid amount of features lots of slots for everything i needed
nice board nave no any issues with 12700k all temps are fine easy oced ram to 3600mhz cl14 patriot steeles 4400

i chose the ddr4 model and do not regret it since it is impossible to find ddr5 on top of that was able to max out the ram with 128gb of fury beast for a fraction of the cost of what ddr5 would have cost very happy with my purchase this review is for the msi review rebate program
amazing board with tons of features absolutely worth the money im rating it 4 stars because the box was a bit damaged and came without bubble bag or foam
very good

good price on a board that worked first time out of the box
seems these days thats rare unfortunately but im glad to say that at least the one i received has been perfect

seems sturdy reasonable price will update once installed
update works well and msi support is alright

definitely happy this has usb bios flash or it would have been a very expensive paperweight after updating the bios to the v11 version when first setting up downgrading back to v10 via usb was the only way to get this working again have since upgraded to v12 and that one has been stable as well
works well for my 12900k no issues so far paired with a 3090
mai motherboard works as intended no issue on fire time start up plenty options for future upgrades

i bought from amazon and had bad luck of a doa mobo had to return it lucky me i found one at my local best buy and can say this is a great mobo combined with a 12700kf 51ghz oc and it runs really smooth

home pc replaced gigabyte z690i ultra ddr4 due to recall tomahawk is pretty solid bios is full of too many settings for me to play with tho to be fair tho easy install and setup is only because i have been doing home builds many years us army trained technician
works great for an i912900k perfect if you dont want to be an early adopter of ddr5 ram which is quite overpriced atm
the wireless card works best when the motherboard is connected to the router via ethernet cable wait a minute

overall it is a good board however the only complaint i have is that mounting for the primary ssd slot heatsink cover fell off it seems like whatever was holding it into the board failed and it came out however you can still use the slot just not the included heatsink that covers it
was excited to finally have all the parts to build my pc but then i open my motherboard socket and see bent andor broken pins very disapointing and frustrating
board overall looked solid but as i went to install m2 drives noticed all the post were unattached from the board
the box came without any bubble wrap or any kindprotection i would expect if i pay around 300 for a mobo for it to atleast be protected will build my pc how it is functional
it posted first try wifi and ethernet didnt work until driver update through the included usb very happy except my temporary ram cant reach its advertised speeds of 3200mhz with this mobo

overall this isnt a bad product just be careful buying through amazon they sent me this motherboard with bent cpu pins a lot of them once i am refunded for this i am buying another motherboard directly from the msi store
cannot connect to internet cannot install drivers without windows update and cannot update windows without internet
box only contained stickers motherboard and installation guide did not come with hardwaremounting screws pci ez screws etc

a screw stud was broken on the motherboard upon arrival i am hoping it wont effect anything as it is just for the heat shield but as of yet nothing is powering on it my be causing the sata to not sit right i am going to have a professional look at the system maybe it can be saved if so ill update the review
when i received it it already broken

ordered the motherboard new on prime day and got sent a clearly used and broken product motherboard came with the socket protector popped offmissing bent pins and thermal paste residue along the locking mechanism accessory bags opened and empty no protective shipping elements in box and motherboard not put into an antistatic bag i am livid
xmp doesnt work out of the box tried rolling back the bios to 11 like people have suggested didnt help oh and it also killed the realtek chip no audio i do not recommend this board
